<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-14166">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Small%20Boat%20Sailing.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11217">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11217 mb-requirement-id-11218">
        (a) Explain to your counselor the most likely hazards you may encounter
        while participating in small-boat sailing activities, and what you
        should do to anticipate, help prevent, mitigate, and respond to these
        hazards. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/BmjUXXB_3UY" target="_blank"
          >Environment, Rules Afloat and General Safety (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11217 mb-requirement-id-11219">
        (b) Review prevention, symptoms, and first-aid treatment for the
        following injuries or illnesses that can occur while sailing: blisters,
        cold-water shock and hypothermia, dehydration, heat-related illnesses,
        sunburn, sprains, and strains. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/rH3gZuSr6Y8" target="_blank"
          >Cold Water Shock (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/EmNieKLjmH4" target="_blank"
          >What Happens if You Don't Drink Enough Water? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Rz6Wxiv4aRAK" target="_blank"
          >Dangers of Heat-Related Illnesses (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/9aFm087_XWg" target="_blank"
          >What Causes Sunburns? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/z1gbB_peVDQ" target="_blank"
          >Sprain Care With RICE Method (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11217 mb-requirement-id-11220">
        (c) Discuss the Scouting America Safety Afloat policy. Tell how it
        applies to small-boat sailing activities. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/health-and-safety/safety-moments/safety-afloat/"
          target="_blank"
          >Safety Afloat (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11242">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Before doing the following requirements, successfully complete the
      Scouting America swimmer test. <br /><br /><b>Note:</b> See the
      <i>Swimming</i> merit badge pamphlet for details about the Scouting
      America swimmer test. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Swimming.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        ><i>Swimming</i> Merit Badge Pamphlet (PDF)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11243">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Describe the boat you will be using for the sailing requirement, naming
      all of the major parts and the function of those parts. <br /><br /><b
        >Note: </b
      >The skills may be demonstrated on any boat available to the Scout;
      sailboards are not acceptable. While no specific sail plan is recommended,
      it is suggested that the craft be smaller than 20 feet. The boat must be
      capsizable and have the capability of sailing to windward. <br /><i
        >Resource:</i
      >
      <a href="https://youtu.be/hJHkil8HOHo" target="_blank"
        >Sailboat Parts Explained: Overview and Names (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11221">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Before going afloat, do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11221 mb-requirement-id-11222">
        (a) Discuss the nine points of the Scouting America Safety Afloat plan.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.scouting.org/health-and-safety/safety-moments/safety-afloat/"
          target="_blank"
          >Safety Afloat (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11221 mb-requirement-id-11223">
        (b) Explain the rules of the road in general and any specific rules or
        laws that apply to your area or state. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/bFPRfYCUYY8" target="_blank"
          >Steering Rules: Crossing, Meeting &amp; Overtaking (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11221 mb-requirement-id-11224">
        (c) Explain how water conditions, the hazards of weather, and heavy
        winds can affect both safety and performance in sailing.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11221 mb-requirement-id-11225">
        (d) Discuss the warning signs of inclement weather and what to do should
        heavy winds develop or a storm approach. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://thenauticalnomad.com/sailing-basics/safety-at-sea/how-to-prepare-for-heavy-weather-conditions/"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Prepare for Heavy Weather Conditions (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/vAqM9g7Chgg" target="_blank"
          >Science of Sailing | Level 3 | Clouds and Breezes (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/OEWQzUl1jQc" target="_blank"
          >How To Read Clouds (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11221 mb-requirement-id-11226">
        (e) Prepare a typical float plan. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/AZHZzy25E-8" target="_blank"
          >Filing a Float Plan (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://floatplancentral.cgaux.org/classroom/preparation.htm"
          target="_blank"
          >How To Complete a Float Plan (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11221 mb-requirement-id-11227">
        (f) Discuss the proper clothing, footwear, and personal gear required
        for small-boat sailing in warm weather and in cool weather. Explain how
        choosing the proper clothing, footwear, and personal gear will help keep
        you comfortable and safe while sailing. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/vzmPjHBZ--g" target="_blank"
          >What To Wear for Dinghy Sailing (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11244">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      Discuss with your counselor how to identify the wind direction and wind
      indicators. Explain the importance of this task before setting sail.
      <br /><i>Resource:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/tIlZv-l9qcQ" target="_blank"
        >Wind Awareness (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11228">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      Following the Scouting America Safety Afloat plan, show that you and a
      buddy can sail a boat properly. Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11228 mb-requirement-id-11229">
        (a) Prepare a boat for sailing, including a safety inspection.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11228 mb-requirement-id-11230">
        (b) Get underway from a dock, mooring, or beach. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/JBdvAG6Ham0" target="_blank"
          >Beach Launching a Single Handed Boat (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11228 mb-requirement-id-11231">
        (c) Properly set sails for a round-trip course approved by your
        counselor that will include running, beating, and reaching-the basic
        points of sail. While sailing, demonstrate good helmsmanship skills.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/Ow-P45DpHj8" target="_blank"
          >Points of Sail (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/mTtKGr_4vYg" target="_blank"
          >Close-Hauled (Sailing Towards the Wind) (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/DsmH7XuMJbw" target="_blank"
          >Reaching (Sailing Across the Wind) (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/FI-9JeVzsK0" target="_blank"
          >Running (Sailing Away From the Wind) (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11228 mb-requirement-id-11232">
        (d) Change direction by tacking; change direction by jibing. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://youtu.be/gMEOex9GQWU" target="_blank"
          >How To Tack (Turn Around) a One Person Sailboat (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/LVQyaWa4riw" target="_blank"
          >How To Jib a Single Person Sailboat (Turning Away From the Wind)
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11228 mb-requirement-id-11233">
        (e) Demonstrate getting out of irons.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11228 mb-requirement-id-11234">
        (f) Demonstrate the safety position.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11228 mb-requirement-id-11235">
        (g) Demonstrate capsize procedures and the rescue of a person overboard.
        <br /><br /><b>Note: </b>Capsize procedures should be conducted under
        the close supervision of the counselor. A rescue boat should be standing
        by to assist, if necessary, and to tow the capsized craft to shore.
        Self-bailing boats are acceptable for this requirement. Extreme care
        should be taken to avoid personal injury and damage to the boat or
        equipment. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/0flyv_GPwwc" target="_blank"
          >Capsize a Single Handed Sailboat (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11228 mb-requirement-id-11236">
        (h) Demonstrate the procedure to take after running aground. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://www.cruisingworld.com/how/what-do-when-you-run-aground/"
          target="_blank"
          >What To Do When You Run Aground (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11228 mb-requirement-id-11237">
        (i) Accept a single line or side tow and maneuver the craft being towed
        safely for 20 boat lengths.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11228 mb-requirement-id-11247">
        (j) Upon returning to the dock, mooring, or beach, properly secure all
        equipment, furl or stow sails, and prepare the craft for unattended
        docking or beaching overnight or longer.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11238">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      Demonstrate a working knowledge of marlinespike seamanship. Do the
      following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11238 mb-requirement-id-11239">
        (a) Show how to tie a square (reef) knot, clove hitch, two half hitches,
        bowline, cleat hitch, and figure-eight knot. Demonstrate the use of
        each. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/L-SWGGN3nsM" target="_blank"
          >Essential Sailing Knots (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=0-eDYx3lkC8" target="_blank"
          >Overhand Knot (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11238 mb-requirement-id-11240">
        (b) Show how to heave a line, coil a line, and fake down a line.
        <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/b14m_BGixK0" target="_blank"
          >How To Coil a Rope (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/X6QWotYflG0" target="_blank"
          >How To Flake and Heave a Line (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-11238 mb-requirement-id-11241">
        (c) Discuss the kinds of lines used on sailboats and the types of fibers
        used in their manufacture. Explain the advantages and disadvantages of
        each. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.sailboat-cruising.com/marine-cordage.html"
          target="_blank"
          >Lines and Usages for Sailing (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11245">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      Describe how you would care for and maintain a sailboat and its gear
      throughout the year.
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-11246">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      With your counselor, review sailing terminology and the points of sail.
      Discuss various types of sailboats in use today and explain their
      differences.
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
